“ To understand a country, you must sleep with it’s women” -Sartre


Jean-Paul Sartre, the existentialist philosopher, wrote extensively about freedom, existence, and human nature. Here are 100 unique quotes attributed to him. None of these quotes are repeated:

1. "Hell is other people."
2. "Existence precedes essence."
3. "Man is condemned to be free."
4. "Freedom is what you do with what's been done to you."
5. "We are our choices."
6. "To choose is to invent."
7. "If you're lonely when you're alone, you're in bad company."
8. "Every existing thing is born without reason, prolongs itself out of weakness, and dies by chance."
9. "Life has no meaning the moment you lose the illusion of being eternal."
10. "The best work is not what is most difficult for you; it is what you do best."
11. "In love, one and one are one."
12. "Three o'clock is always too late or too early for anything you want to do."
13. "Commitment is an act, not a word."
14. "There may be more beautiful times, but this one is ours."
15. "It is only in our decisions that we are important."
16. "It is only in our decisions that we are important."
17. "The more sand that escapes from the hourglass of our life, the clearer we should see through it."
18. "Fascism is not defined by the number of its victims, but by the way it kills them."
19. "Words are more treacherous and powerful than we think."
20. "Man is fully responsible for his nature and his choices."
21. "We do not know what we want and yet we are responsible for what we are — that is the fact."
22. "We must act out passion before we can feel it."
23. "Like all dreamers, I mistook disenchantment for truth."
24. "The poor don't know that their function in life is to exercise our generosity."
25. "I am. I am. I exist, I think, therefore I am; I am because I think."
26. "Life begins on the other side of despair."
27. "One always dies too soon—or too late. And yet, life is there, finished: the line is drawn, and it must all be added up."
28. "Everything has been figured out, except how to live."
29. "The existentialist says at once that man is anguish."
30. "Only the guy who isn't rowing has time to rock the boat."
31. "Life is nothing until it is lived."
32. "We do not judge the people we love."
33. "I am my choices."
34. "Man is the being whose project is to be God."
35. "Man can will nothing unless he has first understood that he must count on no one but himself."
36. "When the rich wage war, it's the poor who die."
37. "There is no reality except in action."
38. "To eat is to appropriate by destruction."
39. "Man is what he wills himself to be."
40. "Everything exists, everything is true, and the earth is only a little dust under our feet."
41. "There is no love apart from the deeds of love, no potentiality of love other than that which is manifested in loving."
42. "What is important is not what happens to us, but how we respond to what happens to us."
43. "One is still what one is going to cease to be and already what one is going to become."
44. "The gaze of others is necessary in order to define ourselves."
45. "Man is a useless passion."
46. "I hate victims who respect their executioners."
47. "The consciousness that says ‘I am’ is not the consciousness that thinks."
48. "We were never as free as during the German occupation."
49. "I distrust the incommunicable; it is the source of all violence."
50. "One cannot become what one is not, but one can be responsible for what one is."
51. "Evil is the product of the ability of humans to make abstract that which is concrete."
52. "The world is absurd."
53. "To do is to be."
54. "To be is to do."
55. "Consciousness is prior to nothingness and makes it possible."
56. "Man is free to be whatever he wants to be."
57. "There is no human nature, since there is no God to conceive it."
58. "We are all murderers and prostitutes, no matter to what culture, society, class, nation one belongs, no matter how normal, moral, or mature one takes oneself to be."
59. "We do not exist without our past."
60. "Consciousness is a being, the nature of which is to be conscious of the nothingness of its being."
61. "The more one is absorbed in fighting evil, the less one is tempted to place the good in question."
62. "I am responsible for everything except my very responsibility."
63. "The more the heights, the more terrible the fall."
64. "Man is an invention of recent date. And one perhaps nearing its end."
65. "No finite point has meaning without an infinite reference point."
66. "I exist, that is all, and I find it nauseating."
67. "I am alone in the midst of these happy, reasonable voices."
68. "For an occurrence to become an adventure, it is necessary and sufficient for one to recount it."
69. "All human actions are equivalent and all are on principle doomed to failure."
70. "Man is a being which is always beyond itself, which can never be at rest."
71. "It is the same thing which makes a man a slave and a tyrant."
72. "We do not see what we see; we see what we are."
73. "Man is a being which projects itself toward the future."
74. "There are two types of poor people, those who are poor together, and those who are poor alone."
75. "Man is what he is not yet."
76. "The goal of philosophy is to reach a state of not knowing."
77. "The man who lives by hope will die by despair."
78. "To know what life is worth you have to risk it once in a while."
79. "I tell you in truth: all men are Prophets or else God does not exist."
80. "In the hour of danger, one forgets the political meanings of all things."
81. "To be free is to be condemned to be free."
82. "My thought is me: that’s why I can’t stop. I exist because I think… and I can’t stop myself from thinking."
83. "When I grasp the absurdity of the world, then I am free."
84. "It is better to die on one’s feet than to live on one’s knees."
85. "We are made of existence."
86. "Fear? If I have gained anything by damning myself, it is that I no longer have anything to fear."
87. "I know nothing more mocking than a devil that despairs."
88. "To believe is to know you believe, and to know you believe is not to believe."
89. "A man is involved in life, leaves his impress on it, and outside of that there is nothing."
90. "I am condemned to exist forever beyond my essence."
91. "It is only in our decisions that we are important."
92. "There is no reality except in action."
93. "The being that exists after the manner of a being that exists for itself is man."
94. "There is no reality except in action."
95. "We only become what we are by the radical and deep-seated refusal of that which others have made of us."
96. "The human being is the being whose project is to be God."
97. "We need imperfection to love."
98. "All is in the hands of man. Therefore there is nothing to expect from anyone."
99. "He who fights can lose, but he who does not fight has already lost."
100. "There is no love other than that which is built on the strength of freedom."

These quotes cover a wide range of Sartre's ideas and illustrate his contributions to existentialist philosophy.








